ZH: 我常常抄近道去上班，可以节省很多时间。
EN: I often take a shortcut to work, which saves a lot of time.

ZH: 昨天我抄近道回家，却进入了一条陌生的街道。
EN: Yesterday, I took a shortcut home and ended up on an unfamiliar street.

ZH: 为了避开车流，他选择抄近道。
EN: To avoid traffic, he chose to take a shortcut.

ZH: 如果你想早点到达目的地，最好抄近道。
EN: If you want to arrive at your destination earlier, it's best to take a shortcut.

ZH: 抄近道可能会让你错过一些风景。
EN: Taking a shortcut may make you miss out on some scenery.

ZH: 她迷路了，所以决定抄近道。
EN: She got lost, so she decided to take a shortcut.

ZH: 抄近道是一种省时的方式。
EN: Taking a shortcut is a time-saving method.

ZH: 我不喜欢抄近道，我喜欢漫步街头看风景。
EN: I don't like taking shortcuts, I enjoy strolling the streets and enjoying the scenery.

ZH: 抄近道并不总是比正常路线快。
EN: Taking a shortcut isn't always faster than the regular route.

ZH: 他习惯了抄近道，不管去哪儿都会尝试一下。
EN: He is used to taking shortcuts and always tries them no matter where he goes.

ZH: 这条小路可以作为一个抄近道，通向山顶。
EN: This path can serve as a shortcut to the mountaintop.

ZH: 这条抄近道比直接走高速公路更快捷。
EN: This shortcut is faster than taking the highway directly.

ZH: 我迷路了，你能告诉我一个抄近道吗？
EN: I'm lost, can you tell me a shortcut?

ZH: 他总是抄近道，所以他的步行时间比别人短很多。
EN: He always takes shortcuts, so his walking time is much shorter than others.

ZH: 我给你一张地图，上面有一些抄近道。
EN: I'll give you a map with some shortcuts marked on it.

ZH: 虽然抄近道达到目的地的时间更短，但是也有风险。
EN: Although taking a shortcut can reach the destination faster, there is also a risk involved.

ZH: 抄近道可以缩短行程时间。
EN: Taking a shortcut can shorten the travel time.

ZH: 我们可以抄近道走，这样可以避开交通堵塞。
EN: We can take a shortcut to avoid traffic congestion.

ZH: 他喜欢抄近道，因为他觉得那样更加刺激。
EN: He likes taking shortcuts because he thinks it's more exciting.

ZH: 虽然抄近道不是最安全的选择，但是有时候是非常有效的。
EN: Although taking shortcuts is not the safest choice, sometimes it is very effective.

ZH: 别人都说抄近道很危险，但我觉得那只是他们不敢尝试。
EN: Others say that taking shortcuts is dangerous, but I think it's just because they are afraid to try.
